SENATE JOINT RESOLUTION 790
By Southerland
A RESOLUTION to honor and commend Sophia Mangin, the choir
teacher at Morristown-Hamblen West High
School.
WHEREAS, the members of this General Assembly are pleased to recognize and
commend those successful teachers of the arts who, through their natural talents and
extraordinary efforts, bring the joys of creative expression and culture to the students of this
State while promoting the importance of the performing arts; and
WHEREAS, one such estimable individual is Sophia Mangin, a choir instructor of
extraordinary talent, skill, and dedication at Morristown-Hamblen West High School; and
WHEREAS, a professional of the greatest ability and integrity, Ms. Mangin is the proud
teacher of five students who were recently named to the Tennessee Music Education
Association All-State choir in recognition of their excellence as vocalists; and
WHEREAS, Ms. Mangin truly epitomizes the devoted teacher who is wholly committed
to the highest ideals and quality education for all; and
WHEREAS, she serves as an inspiration to her colleagues and students alike, and it is
appropriate that we recognize her; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE ONE HUNDRED FOURTEENTH
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE HOUSE OF
REPRESENTATIVES CONCURRING, that we honor and congratulate Sophia Mangin, the choir
teacher at Morristown-Hamblen West High School, for her exceptional service to the children of
Tennessee, salute her professional expertise and personal excellence, and wish her all the best
in her future endeavors.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
